00:00:00.720 --> 00:00:05.460
Which of the following triangles
are similar to triangle ABC?

00:00:05.460 --> 00:00:08.260
So this is triangle ABC.

00:00:08.260 --> 00:00:10.280
Before we even look
at these options,

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:13.560
let's remind ourselves of what
it means for two triangles

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:14.280
to be similar.

00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:16.215
There's multiple ways
of thinking about it.

00:00:16.215 --> 00:00:19.600
The classical definition
of similar triangles

00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:22.710
is that all the corresponding
angles are equivalent.

00:00:22.710 --> 00:00:26.890
So for example, if these
two are similar triangles,

00:00:26.890 --> 00:00:29.360
then if this angle
corresponds to that one,

00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:31.450
then these two angles
are going to be the same.

00:00:31.450 --> 00:00:33.060
If this angle
corresponds to this one,

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:35.400
then these two angles
are going to be the same.

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:39.032
And if this angle
corresponds to this one,

00:00:39.032 --> 00:00:40.990
then these two angles
are going to be the same,

00:00:40.990 --> 00:00:42.450
and these are similar.

00:00:42.450 --> 00:00:44.991
And the reason why similarity
is useful is because that tells

00:00:44.991 --> 00:00:46.820
you the ratio between
corresponding sides

00:00:46.820 --> 00:00:48.570
are going to be the same.

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:51.820
So for example, if this side
has length 2 and this side

00:00:51.820 --> 00:00:54.660
has length 1, then the ratio
of this side to this side

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:55.850
is 2 to 1.

00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:58.730
The corresponding sides here
are this side and this side.

00:00:58.730 --> 00:01:01.580
So they would also have
to have a 2 to 1 ratio.

00:01:01.580 --> 00:01:04.786
So for example, this could
be 4, and this could be 2-- 2

00:01:04.786 --> 00:01:05.660
to 1 ratio.

00:01:05.660 --> 00:01:08.050
4/2 is the same thing as 2/1.

00:01:08.050 --> 00:01:11.670
Or it could be 7 to 3 and 1/2.

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:16.030
Or it could be 10 to 5.

00:01:16.030 --> 00:01:19.230
It would always have a 2 to
1 ratio if this had a 2 to 1

00:01:19.230 --> 00:01:21.740
ratio and if these
are similar triangles.

00:01:21.740 --> 00:01:23.512
Now, in the context
of a line and slope,

00:01:23.512 --> 00:01:25.220
I'll think about
another one, another way

00:01:25.220 --> 00:01:27.000
of thinking about similarity.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:31.580
If you have two
right triangles--

00:01:31.580 --> 00:01:34.620
so let's say this is one right
triangle right over here--

00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:37.090
so if you have one right
triangle right over there

00:01:37.090 --> 00:01:43.200
and you have another right
triangle just like that,

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:48.740
if you have two right triangles
and the ratio of the two

00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:50.954
sides on either side
of the right angle

00:01:50.954 --> 00:01:53.370
correspond to each other-- so
if the ratio of this magenta

00:01:53.370 --> 00:01:59.460
